Comment: 0,0:01:45.88,0:01:45.88,Main,,0,0,0,,{Title}
Comment: 0,0:01:54.89,0:01:54.89,Main,,0,0,0,,{Part A}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.24,0:02:01.76,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,We must find out \N who they are at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.46,0:02:07.19,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,They aren’t trying to take \N the Rose Bride.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.19,0:02:09.45,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,They’re trying to kill her!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.45,0:02:12.38,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,Needless to say, it is our duty \N to maintain order in the academy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.38,0:02:16.07,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,as representatives of the student body \N and executives of the Student Council.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.07,0:02:18.62,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,Seriously... \N Who {\i1}are{\i0} these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.07,0:02:23.69,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,{\q2}Manipulating ordinary students and making them \N duel Tenjou Utena one after another...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.69,0:02:25.54,Main,Juri,0,0,0,,You sound irritated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.05,0:02:29.13,Main,Juri,0,0,0,,Is it because your friends, \N and even Touga, have been targeted?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.13,0:02:31.88,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,Always keeping yourself \N in the know, aren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.88,0:02:34.45,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,But if your network of information \N is {\i1}that{\i0} good,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.45,0:02:37.22,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,then I want you to find out \N who these people are, and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.08,0:02:43.31,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,We have one clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.31,0:02:48.65,Main,Juri,0,0,0,,Only someone chosen by The End of the World \N {should be able}is supposed to have a Rose Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.16,0:02:53.82,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,So our lurker in the shadows \N could in fact be The End of the World, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:54.57,Main,Juri,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.57,0:02:56.97,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,But if you think about \N all the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.97,0:03:00.49,Main,Nanami,0,0,0,,it’s obviously someone \N who has backing from The End of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:06.37,Main,Miki,0,0,0,,In any case, that someone \N must be within the academy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.14,0:03:11.30,Main,Juri,0,0,0,,Sorry, \N I couldn’t hear you very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.47,0:03:16.26,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Chu-Chu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.26,0:03:18.05,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Chu-Chu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:20.05,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Here, Chu-Chu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:23.94,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Man... \N Where could he be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.70,0:03:26.87,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Is this little one yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.15,0:03:30.82,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Oh, Chu-Chu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.38,0:03:33.40,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.56,0:03:41.37,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Thank you so much. \N Did he cause you any trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.37,0:03:42.71,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.71,0:03:45.92,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,I found him caught \N in a mousetrap in the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:47.03,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,He was crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:48.89,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,A mousetrap?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.89,0:03:51.31,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Could you behave \N once in a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.31,0:03:52.59,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Ms. Tenjou Utena...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:55.87,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,How do you know \N my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.39,0:03:57.73,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,It’s a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.73,0:04:00.43,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,I have been interested in you \N for quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.87,0:04:03.76,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,I’m Mikage Souji, \N from the high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.76,0:04:05.10,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Mikage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.10,0:04:09.10,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,So you’re the genius high schooler \N who runs the Mikage Seminar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:16.31,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,What do you say, \N Ms. Tenjou Utena?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:18.65,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t you like to \N join my seminar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.65,0:04:19.82,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Huh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.68,0:04:24.74,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,I— See, last test I took \N was a {\i1}make-up test.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.50,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,This has nothing to do \N with academic skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.50,0:04:29.33,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,My seminar always seeks out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:32.00,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,...those with unique personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.13,0:04:36.51,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,You’re more than welcome \N to come and look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:41.26,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,This building is where \N you hold your seminar, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.16,0:04:43.43,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:44.51,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Nemuro Memorial Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.92,0:04:50.62,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,I imagine you’ve heard the tales \N they tell about this building, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:51.45,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:58.95,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,If you’re thinking of the story about \N one hundred boys dying here, {it’s true.}that one is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.93,0:05:03.14,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Long ago, there was a man \N called Professor Nemuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.68,0:05:05.31,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,There was a fire here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.31,0:05:08.66,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,His students were trapped inside \N and burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.77,0:05:14.34,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,The building was later renovated \N into the Nemuro Memorial Hall we have now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.97,0:05:15.81,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.07,0:05:20.73,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,...that happened long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.63,0:05:24.14,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.14,0:05:26.72,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Mr. Akio? Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.55,0:05:30.85,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,He’s not here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:33.06,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,That’s weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.28,0:05:50.25,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,It’s you...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.09,0:05:58.54,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,All I did was \N make a deal with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:00.52,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,I have no obligation{original: reason} \N to obey your orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.52,0:06:01.32,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.32,0:06:02.80,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,That is our contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:04.59,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Ever since that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:17.61,Main,Student,0,0,0,,It seems to be sticking around, \N doesn’t it, Professor Nemuro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.19,0:06:20.13,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Hmm? What does?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.13,0:06:21.94,Main,Student,0,0,0,,I was talking about the snow, \N professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.94,0:06:23.93,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Stop calling me “professor”.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.93,0:06:25.67,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,We’re not apart in age, you know. {lit. 'Our age is not different'}{Alt: We are the same age, you know.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.94,Main,Student,0,0,0,,Distinctions are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.60,0:06:32.16,Main,Student,0,0,0,,With a genius like you here, \N this has really gotten off the ground. {kore}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.16,0:06:34.83,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Really, now... \N You give me too much credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.71,0:06:39.65,Main,Student,0,0,0,,In any case, I didn’t think they would be \N this extreme with the secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.65,0:06:41.59,Main,Student,0,0,0,,They treat us like \N parts in a machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.06,0:06:45.09,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Didn’t you agree to that \N in the contract with the academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:49.48,Main,Student,0,0,0,,But we don’t even know \N what the section next to us is researching.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.48,0:06:52.21,Main,Student,0,0,0,,Rumors say it’s about \N “the power to revolutionize the world”,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.21,0:06:55.10,Main,Student,0,0,0,,or some research on \N “attaining eternity”.{永遠を手に入れる phrasing ("attain(ing) eternity") - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.95,0:06:58.37,Main,Student,0,0,0,,Can’t you even give us a hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:01.07,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Even I know nothing \N beyond the rumors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.07,0:07:03.11,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,And I care not to know more.{And I don't/do not care to know more.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:06.78,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Incidentally, there’s something \N I’ve been meaning to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.37,0:07:08.70,Main,Student,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.70,0:07:13.45,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,What are those rings \N you all wear on your left ring fingers?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.24,0:07:16.20,Main,Student,0,0,0,,They don’t have \N a particular meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.20,0:07:18.00,Main,Student,0,0,0,,They’re just the latest fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.33,0:07:21.31,Main,Student,0,0,0,,So that’s the genius \N Professor Nemuro?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.31,0:07:23.80,Main,Student,0,0,0,,And he really doesn’t know \N about what we’re doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.15,0:07:25.58,Main,Student,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.58,0:07:28.80,Main,Student,0,0,0,,And yet... {\i1}you-know-who{\i0} \N vouches for his intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:32.08,Main,Student,0,0,0,,His thesis is interesting, \N but the man himself is pretty dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.08,0:07:35.31,Main,Student,0,0,0,,People who pretend to not care \N about anything lack experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.31,0:07:37.04,Main,Student,0,0,0,,Let him put on airs \N as much as he wants.{Yoshino Hiroyuki!!!!!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.04,0:07:38.77,Main,Student,0,0,0,,The man’s practically a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.30,0:07:41.43,Main,Student,0,0,0,,We should get as much use \N as we can out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.58,0:07:48.15,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,At the time, \N I certainly was more computer than man. {At the time, I certainly was a computer-like man.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.15,0:07:51.78,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Computers are peerless machines, \N but machines on their own lack purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:55.01,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,The dry days of a dry man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.01,0:07:58.79,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,And it is also true that I was not very \N interested in the research at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:02.88,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,The fact that what I was tasked with \N wasn’t progressing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.88,0:08:05.09,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,...also made no difference to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:09.26,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,You’re the research coordinator, \N Professor Nemuro, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.01,0:08:13.68,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,The Board of Directors sent me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.20,0:08:18.34,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I’ve been assigned as the new inspector. \N I’m Chida Tokiko. Pleased to meet you.{Lit. This time I will be fulfilling the role of the inspector.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.97,0:08:28.99,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,The streets around here are awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.70,0:08:32.04,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,The slush must make things difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.04,0:08:33.49,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Yes, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.35,0:08:40.59,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,So, what did you need \N that required me to come to your house?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:43.09,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Too strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:49.51,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,{\q2}The tea seems a little too strong... even though \N I let it steep the same amount of time I usually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:52.89,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I wonder, is it possible \N for an hourglass to run slow?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.31,0:08:57.88,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,The job assigned to me \N is proceeding as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.88,0:09:01.10,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,However, I can’t guarantee \N that it will be completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:06.19,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I know you’re not the type of person \N to take orders from others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.59,0:09:08.82,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Genius is something divine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.82,0:09:12.07,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Its essence can’t be tied down \N to this world.{Alt: The soul of ingenuity can’t be restrained to the mortal plane.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.68,0:09:15.24,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,I’m not a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.24,0:09:18.73,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Why are you working \N on this assignment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.73,0:09:20.88,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Purely for business reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.88,0:09:26.09,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,As it is, I think I’m doing more \N than my contract calls for.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.61,0:09:31.04,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,We have one hundred extraordinary boys \N assembled at Ohtori Academy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.04,0:09:32.55,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,all pursuing this. {kore}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:37.06,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,They say the research is a path to \N the power to revolutionize the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.07,0:09:41.07,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,or to attain eternity, \N or something of the such.{永遠を手に入れる phrasing ("attain eternity") - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.27,0:09:46.62,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,To even think of \N attaining eternity...{永遠を手に入れ phrasing ("attain(ing) eternity") - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:49.65,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Makes it sound like they’re building \N a perpetual motion machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.09,0:09:56.05,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,People should be humbly grateful \N for what God grants them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:59.66,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,But if it’s you, surely...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.90,0:10:03.67,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Excuse me just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.61,0:10:09.07,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Mamiya! \N What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.03,0:10:15.10,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Weren’t you told \N to rest in bed for the day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:17.93,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Yes... But I got a little worried \N about the roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:20.90,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Go back to bed right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.90,0:10:23.25,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Yes... In a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.25,0:10:27.35,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,There’s nothing I hate more than someone \N who neglects their own well-being!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:34.86,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Sorry you had to see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.08,0:10:37.68,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Hurry up and go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.35,0:10:42.98,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Professor Nemuro?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.61,0:10:44.91,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,You are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:48.00,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I’m Chida Tokiko’s \N little brother, Mamiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.46,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,For the longest time \N I’ve really wanted to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.46,0:10:53.85,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Because of the interesting \N and odd rumors?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.85,0:10:56.42,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,They say I’m more computer than man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.42,0:10:58.26,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I’ve read your thesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:02.52,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,You’re the first person \N I’ve ever looked up to aside from my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:10.05,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,My sister came to Ohtori Academy \N to meet you.
Comment: 0,0:11:10.65,0:11:10.65,Main,,0,0,0,,{Eyecatch}
Comment: 0,0:11:27.67,0:11:27.67,Main,,0,0,0,,{Part B}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:34.42,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I have to do this since \N you won’t sleep like you’re told to.{More truncated/generalized alt: since you don’t do as you’re told.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.89,0:11:37.19,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I like it when you \N give me injections.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.19,0:11:39.97,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Don’t say such silly things, \N little troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.82,0:11:45.18,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,It’s for his sake... \N that I involved myself in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.63,0:11:50.15,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,There’s nothing left \N but to accept there is no hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.15,0:11:52.19,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,or so the doctors tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.77,0:11:55.06,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,But if {\i1}that{\i0} {bears fruit}proves successful...{are}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.84,0:11:58.80,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,That has nothing to do \N with medicine. {are}{it kind of bugs me, that most of the time they say 'that' instead of research. Not sure if they're not implying that it's not quite research. I've labelled all instances I could find with are and kore in the comments as aproppriate}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.35,0:12:03.46,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Even if it proves successful, \N it’s not like it will cure your brother’s illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.46,0:12:04.61,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:07.21,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Maybe I could \N attain eternity for him.{永遠を手に入れ phrasing ("attain(ing) eternity") - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.20,0:12:15.34,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I’m sorry \N for crying like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.80,0:12:17.05,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:20.68,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,It feels like this is the first time \N I’ve ever seen someone shed tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.22,0:12:24.67,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Is there someone in your life \N who’s important to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.32,0:12:32.77,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Or is it perhaps impossible for someone \N lauded as a genius to love another?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:38.22,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Indeed. {he's not necessarily saying it's impossible, he could be agreeing that her question is a good one to ask. - MT}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.40,0:12:44.16,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Up until today, \N that had been the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:48.87,Main,Human being,0,0,0,,Professor Nemuro has been \N very eager about the project lately, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.86,0:12:53.21,Main,Human being,0,0,0,,The Board of Directors \N sent an inspector, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:56.25,Main,Human being,0,0,0,,She certainly seems to be \N the right one for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.25,0:12:59.59,Main,Human being,0,0,0,,Well, you-know-who \N never makes a pointless move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.87,0:13:07.34,Main,Human being,0,0,0,,Then, does the professor \N still not know what this is all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.17,0:13:16.15,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Is it fine that \N you’re not resting right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.15,0:13:20.46,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Yes. I feel a little better today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.46,0:13:21.24,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.39,0:13:26.83,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,The snow in this garden \N seems to be sticking around, doesn’t it?{ここの庭の雪はなかなか消えないね | Calls back to the line at 6 minutes & 14 seconds (しばらくは消えないでしょうね根室教授). - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.78,0:13:30.65,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,My sister was called away \N by the Board of Directors,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.65,0:13:33.25,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,so she’ll likely \N be gone until evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:35.89,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,That’s just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.89,0:13:38.21,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Today, I’m here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.75,0:13:40.80,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Here. Do you like them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.19,0:13:42.88,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,They’re sugar-preserved roses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.88,0:13:44.80,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,My sister makes them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:47.68,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,These dried flowers \N are like them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.96,0:13:53.71,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,She doesn’t like to see \N the flowers stricken with age.{She doesn’t like to see the flowers pass away.}{あの人は花が散るのを見たくないんですよ | uses 散 just like the duel rules as stated in episodes 1, 2, and 10. We handled those as "stricken" (in the other conjugation used). Tried working around it here (perhaps too loosely) while still leaving a connecting thread since it'll come back next episode, though I don't think it's integral here since it's not making direct reference to the duel rules. - Toa}{Chiru is to scatter. But you wouldn't say to scatter a rose for the duel in english, while it sounds normal in jp. And then they also metaphorically use it to mean that a flower dies, no matter how it dies really. So, yeah, this might be a good solution. - MT}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.43,0:13:59.61,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Like this, even short-lived flowers \N can be made to last a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:01.90,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.90,0:14:05.73,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I wonder if the flowers are happy \N being forced to go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.59,0:14:09.11,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Eternity does not exist \N in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.62,0:14:10.77,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,And yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.77,0:14:14.60,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,...people find \N the pursuit of eternity beautiful.{he's saying mikage is only doing this coz he likes his sis, and he only likes her because she yearned for eternity}{the beauty of the ideal leads people to pursue it nonetheless}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.11,0:14:19.76,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,You don’t expect what your sister \N and I are doing to succeed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.98,0:14:25.78,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I look up to both of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.78,0:14:27.71,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,and I’m grateful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.76,0:14:33.19,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,I should be going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:34.27,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,I’ll be back sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.13,0:14:36.73,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Professor Nemuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.46,0:14:44.49,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,I’ll be sure to tell my sister \N that you’re worried about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:08.18,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,You still can’t solve that equation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:15.60,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Outsiders aren’t allowed in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:17.63,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,There are no outsiders here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:19.70,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,That is, aside from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.70,0:15:20.33,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.70,0:15:25.20,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,That is the first step towards \N the power to revolutionize the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.20,0:15:27.87,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,That will set everything in motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.11,0:15:37.04,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Ridiculous...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.51,0:15:39.33,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,How can you expect anyone \N to do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.86,0:15:43.89,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Isn’t that... \N the ring everyone wears?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.89,0:15:45.42,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,The Rose Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:49.24,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,The proof of a contract \N made with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.24,0:15:50.06,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.06,0:15:51.20,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:55.64,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,All one hundred boys who work here \N are contracted to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.15,0:15:59.70,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,That’s insane... \N What is this contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.70,0:16:03.65,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Those boys bound by contract... \N Why are you subjecting them to this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:09.20,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Besides that... Even if I do attain eternity \N doing this, it won’t make her happy.{永遠を手に入れ phrasing ("attain(ing) eternity") - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.20,0:16:11.07,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,“Her”, hmm? {Fan TL: Ah, yes, her... | Official TL: “Her”, you say?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.11,0:16:15.08,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,I leave you this Rose Seal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.45,0:16:18.66,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Should you desire eternity, \N put it on your finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:23.58,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Your one choice \N is to revolutionize the world.{This episode: 君は世界を革命するしかないだろう}{Previous seminar episodes: あなたは世界を革命するしかないでしょう (except for 17, which uses あなたは世界を革命するしかないでしょ though that could just be a CC error).}{Darou is just more rude than deshou. Which is fine since Akio is in a position of power, though Mikage doesn't really know that at this point. - MT}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.84,0:16:27.60,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,A path has been made ready for you.{This episode: 君の進む道は用意してある}{Previous seminar episodes: あなたの進む道は用意してあります (except for 18, which has あなたの進むべき道は用意してあります).}{aru - casual/rude, arimasu - polite, beki - should - MT}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.94,0:17:23.94,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Is it true?! \N Did you do this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:27.85,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Were you... behind this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.59,0:17:29.19,Main,Mamiya,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.03,0:17:31.82,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.70,0:17:35.03,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,How could you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.01,0:17:38.04,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,They had a contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:44.96,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Ancient creatures died and became fossil fuels, \N like coal and petroleum.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:49.46,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Without that sacrifice, our present \N civilization of energy{alt: energy-dependent civilization} would not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.29,0:17:52.72,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Such sacrifices are always called for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.41,0:17:54.67,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.41,0:17:58.43,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,This is the first step \N in the job you are advancing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:03.94,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,In soon opening the path to eternity \N from this academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.61,0:18:09.12,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Mr. Nemuro...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:11.45,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Mamiya did \N as he was supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.13,0:18:14.82,Main,Nemuro,0,0,0,,Now I, too, \N wish to attempt to attain eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:09.54,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Extra! Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:20.31,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,It’s finished! An all-purpose robot \N built from the very essence of science!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.31,0:19:22.71,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot does not age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.71,0:19:24.70,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot does not tire;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:26.31,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,catches monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:28.90,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,You are superior to humans!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.90,0:19:31.07,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot is superior;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.07,0:19:33.19,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,catches many monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.19,0:19:35.45,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,You will never become worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.45,0:19:37.68,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot does not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.68,0:19:39.91,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,When a monkey is spotted, \N it is caught promptly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.91,0:19:42.53,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot does not feel lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.54,0:19:45.68,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,...because robot has \N all the captured monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.68,0:19:48.61,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot can work indefinitely;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:50.46,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,can catch many monkeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.65,0:19:56.27,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,But looking at you \N makes us feel lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.27,0:19:58.97,Main,C-ko,0,0,0,,Robot has monkeys. \N Robot has monkeys.{Unclear if this means I've found a new monkey to catch or I have monkeys (I'm not lonely!), or do you need a monkey (since you just said you're lonely). You can pick one, or find a way to make it more ambiguous.}{Last one might be ruled out by the captions not having a question mark, unless it's the kind of sentence that can be taken as a question without actually being one. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.94,0:20:08.35,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,It’s you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.35,0:20:09.83,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,It’s been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.83,0:20:12.69,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,The academy has changed a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.72,0:20:16.82,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Just now, I saw \N Professor Nemuro over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.43,0:20:27.28,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Look, you don’t have to do \N what these mysterious people tell you to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:29.90,Main,Anthy,0,0,0,,But it isn’t up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.46,0:20:32.67,Main,Anthy,0,0,0,,I am the Rose Bride, \N after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.67,0:20:33.67,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Dummy!{You’re being dumb!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:43.40,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,There’s nothing I hate more than people \N who don’t care about their own well-being! {自分のことを大事にしないやつが僕は いちばん嫌いなんだ}{Calls back to Tokiko's line from 10:23, but it's a little different. Tokiko's line is 自分のことを大事にしない人が私は いちばん嫌いなの！ which uses hito instead of yatsu, and a different pronoun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:50.02,Main,Mikage,0,0,0,,Tokiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.96,0:20:55.82,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Just like you, he hasn’t \N aged a day since then, has he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:58.51,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Those who stay in this garden \N we call our academy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.51,0:21:00.49,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,...will never become adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.93,0:21:04.13,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Whatever this is... \N is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.13,0:21:07.28,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Are you leading a normal life?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.05,0:21:10.48,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.48,0:21:13.88,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,My husband is a kind person. \N He’s good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.99,0:21:16.25,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,What brought you here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.76,0:21:20.63,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,I came to visit my little brother— \N Mamiya’s— grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.44,0:21:35.17,Main,Tokiko,0,0,0,,Say... Surely you know that to bear fruit, \N flowers have their petals stricken from them. {chiru again - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.17,0:21:36.32,Main,Akio,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Comment: 0,0:21:41.28,0:21:41.28,Main,,0,0,0,,{Ending}
Comment: 0,0:22:56.35,0:22:56.35,Main,,0,0,0,,{Preview}
Dialogue: 1,0:22:58.86,0:23:01.57,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Ms. Kanae, Kozue, Wakaba...
Dialogue: 1,0:23:02.08,0:23:05.65,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Who could be the puppet master \N pulling their strings and making them fight?{forcing them to fight against their will?}
Dialogue: 1,0:23:05.65,0:23:07.77,Main,Anthy,0,0,0,,I’m afraid I myself \N don’t know.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:07.77,0:23:08.47,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 1,0:23:08.47,0:23:13.12,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,That genius high schooler from Nemuro \N Memorial Hall said he’d help me with anything.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:13.12,0:23:15.95,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Mikage Souji... Guess I’ll try to \N work up courage to {consult with}ask him.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:15.95,0:23:18.13,Main,Anthy,0,0,0,,Sure. Whatever you {say}wish, Master Utena.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:18.13,0:23:20.38,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,Next time, \N on Revolutionary Girl Utena:
Dialogue: 1,0:23:20.38,0:23:21.70,Main,Utena,0,0,0,,“The Qualifications of a Duelist”
Dialogue: 1,0:23:21.70,0:23:23.38,Main,Anthy,0,0,0,,The absolute destiny: apocalypse.
